 the in-theater viewing experience by offering unique and exclusive film screenings made available only for the event. <\/p>\n<p>The celebration is set to kick off around noon with a poster sale in the parking lot of the Pageant Theater, where their collection will be made available for a price of $5 per poster. While browsing the posters accumulated by the venue over the last year, attendees will have access to popcorn, drinks and live music.<\/p>\n<p>From there, guests can dive into a trio of remastered films sure to bring intrigue to all and even hints of nostalgia to some. A remastered version of Terry Gilliam&#8217;s &#8220;Time Bandits&#8221; will offer entertainment for the whole family during the event&#8217;s matinee time slot. <\/p>\n<p>Music fans won&#8217;t want to miss Brendan Toller&#8217;s &#8220;Danny Says,&#8221; which details the life and influence of &#8220;punk pioneer&#8221; Danny Fields. Prior to the documentary featuring the former manager of acts like The Stooges and The Ramones, Chico&#8217;s own singer-songwriter, Jonathan Richman, will participate in an extraordinary Q&amp;A detailing his personal experiences with Fields.<\/p>\n<p>Pageant Theater owner Miles Montalbano confessed this moment will be one for the books. <\/p>\n<p>&#8220;I&#8217;m really excited about having Jonathan here to talk about the Danny Fields movie because he was actually a participant in the film. He has such an amazing presence and the best stories, so that&#8217;s going to be pretty neat,&#8221; he said. <\/p>\n<p>The grand finale will include a showing of the remastered supernatural horror motion picture, &#8220;Phantasm&#8221; originally directed by Don Coscarelli and restored by J.J. Abrams. This screening will also include a live stream discussion with the film&#8217;s creators. <\/p>\n<p>Tickets to these films can be purchased individually at the Pageant Theater box office only, where prices range from $7 to $8 depending on the film. More information can be found by visiting the Pageant Theater <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"http:\/\/pageantchico.com\/AHTD.html\">website<\/a> or <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https:\/\/www.facebook.com\/PageantChico\/\">Facebook page<\/a>. <\/p>\n<div id=\"attachment_58418\" style=\"width: 485px\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\"><a href=\"http:\/\/theorion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/pageanttheater.jpg\" rel=\"attachment wp-att-58418\"><img alt=\"pageanttheater.jpg\" src=\"http:\/\/theorion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/pageanttheater-475x176.jpg\" data-uniq-id=\"6f866\" width=\"475\" height=\"176\" class=\"aligncenter wp-image-58418 size-medium\" srcset=\"http:\/\/theorion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/pageanttheater-475x176.jpg 475w, http:\/\/theorion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/pageanttheater-768x285.jpg 768w, http:\/\/theorion.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2016\/09\/pageanttheater.jpg 850w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 475px) 100vw, 475px\" \/><\/a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Photo courtesy of the Pageant Theater&#39;s official Facebook page<\/p><\/div>\n<p><b>Rylee Pedotti can be reached at <\/b>artseditor@theorion.com or @theorion_news<a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https:\/\/twitter.com\/gjohnston786\"> <\/a>on Twitter.<\/p>\n<div class=\"pvc_clear\"><\/div>\n<p id=\"pvc_stats_58416\" class=\"pvc_stats \" element-id=\"58416\"><img src=\"http:\/\/theorion.com\/wp-content\/plugins\/page-views-count\/ajax-loader.gif\" border=0 \/><\/p>\n<div class=\"pvc_clear\"><\/div>\n"},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>On Sept. 24, venues across the nation are set to commemorate independent theaters and their everlasting contributions to cinematic culture. Locals will have their chance to join the celebration as Chico&#8217;s Pageant Theater will be participating in the inaugural Art House Theater Day. Mirrored after music&#8217;s Record Store Day, the film interpretation looks to honor [&hellip;]\n<div class=\"pvc_clear\"><\/div>\n<p id=\"pvc_s